<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-55698" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://richardpettigrew.substack.com/p/formal-methods-in-philosophy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">“It is not uncommon to open an analytic philosophy paper written during the past century and find logical symbols and mathematical notation among the prose… Why do analytic philosophers do this?”</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; Richard Pettigrew answers</span></li>
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-55693" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://journals.publishing.umich.edu/phimp/article/id/4939/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">“Much to many philosophers’ chagrin, the true can and does come apart from the good, the beautiful, and even the useful”</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; Devin Sanchez Curry on &#8220;how folk psychology appropriates scientific concepts&#8221;, focusing on the concept of IQ</span></li>
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-55687" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://www.amazon.com/live/video/05325d038da84e27bb9feb7f1e48b769?_encoding=UTF8&amp;content-id=amzn1.sym.bf108d40-624c-4daa-a054-dc48a9d16b5a&amp;pd_rd_r=9f51b7ae-90d3-4092-a7e3-a33645571532&amp;pd_rd_w=Dj8iN&amp;pd_rd_wg=Jzeqp&amp;ref=vse_cards_0" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">“This is the perfect book for you”</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; a review of Brandom&#8217;s &#8220;Perspectives on Pragmatism&#8221; like no other</span></li>
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-55689" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://arxiv.org/html/2511.15304v1" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">“In Book X of The Republic, Plato excludes poets on the grounds that mimetic language can distort judgment and bring society to a collapse”</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; a new study suggests that in a world running on LLM&#8217;s like ChatGPT, this may be literally true (via MeFi)</span></li>
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-55669" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://www.science.org/doi/10.1126/sciadv.abo0038" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">“People who disagree most with the scientific consensus know less about the relevant issues, but they think they know more”</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; a new study (via MR)</span></li>
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-55651" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://celineleboeuf.substack.com/p/nancy-sherman" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">“I… see philosophy as a practical pursuit and I try to teach in a way that conveys the importance of developing not just intellectual competence, but healthy emotions and healthy relationships”</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; Nancy Sherman on &#8220;Why Philosophy?&#8221;</span></li>
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-55612" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2025/11/17/opinion/her-film-chatbots-romance.html?unlocked_article_code=1.108.Z3K-.skKrDF1ezSW2&amp;smid=url-share" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">AI girlfriends and boyfriends “will wreak havoc on our mental health and relationships”</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; &#8220;Governments should classify these chatbots not simply as another form of media, but as a dependency-fostering product with known psychological risks, like gambling or tobacco&#8221;</span></li>
</ol>
<p>Mini-Heap posts usually appear when several new items accumulate in the <a class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://dailynous.com/heap-of-links/">Heap of Links</a>, a collection of items from around the web that may be of interest to philosophers. The Heap of Links consists partly of suggestions from readers; if you find something online that you think would be of interest to the philosophical community, please <a class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="mailto:dailynouseditor@gmail.com">send it in</a> for consideration for the Heap. Thank you.<br class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image" /><a class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://dailynous.com/2025/11/17/mini-heap-689/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Previous edition</a>.</p><p>The post <a href="https://dailynous.com/2025/11/24/mini-heap-690/">Mini-Heap</a> first appeared on <a href="https://dailynous.com">Daily Nous</a>.</p>